Student Agency long-distance buses do not have standing seats; this has been confirmed by the director of the company Radim Janura.
"This is an issue that we have dealt with with the Ministry and, at the beginning, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got passengers to go to the toilet on the way on condition that they have their own seat," he revealed his position.
The law ignores the steward
"There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the role of steward - there is no legal requirement for this role.
On the other hand, there is also no legal requirement to prevent the carrier from offering services.
The Road Transport Act is limited to the term vehicle receiver; it does not define its rights and duties," adds more generally the spokesman Hanzelka.
Josef Pokorna, the director of the Road Vehicle Traffic Department, believes, on the contrary, that the law adequately addresses the issue.
"It all depends on whether the coach is authorized to propose standing places in its approval.
