In the event that somniloquia becomes very common, it would be advisable to observe the child and consult a specialist, to check whether there is a problem that causes a lot of anxiety and in order to get an explanation for this problem.
We said that this is a benign alteration, which is why there is no treatment, unless it is related to another altered sleep that can be cured (for example, if it is related to sleep apnoea or stress).
What can be done is to take into account a number of very simple preventive measures such as:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
Therefore, look for quiet games and avoid more or less violent programmes or television series.
With children who are very nervous and have difficulty relaxing, relaxation techniques can be used to help them calm down internally.
This will allow the child to have a more peaceful sleep.
As soon as the somniloquies appear try to remain calm.
Remember that they are harmless to the child and the next day he will no longer remember what happened.
Useful advice
Don't wake him up.
It's useless because he's unconscious and you'd wake him up.
Even if he speaks, he sleeps and rests.
Remember that if you are very anxious several times, it is advisable to consult a doctor or check what causes so much anxiety in the child.
If you understand what he says (which is not usual), do not have the temptation to question him for information.
You won't get anything, because by sleeping, he's not conscious to be able to organize his thoughts.
Moreover, you will hear what he says, but you will not know what he is dreaming about, so pay attention to the way in which you interpret the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Never tell the child that you can interview him at night to know his secrets.
Not even joking.
This causes a lot of anxiety.
In conclusion, don't worry, it's nothing very bad, it's an episode that lasts only a few minutes.
