We must also review existing control systems in the light of scientific opinion, so that they are fully effective and can follow up on new technologies."
Brussels asked the Independent Scientific Committee to examine the problem, in view of the intensive use of portable music devices and the increase in the number of young people exposed to the noise they generate.
'Scientists-concluded executive Ue- confirm that there are good reasons to be concerned, and that the European Commission will now discuss with Member States and other interested parties , what measures could possibly be adopted to better protect children and adolescents from exposure to noise from portable music devices and similar devices.
