It is possible to limit these data using solutions such as the reduction of noise exposure levels and duration.
The Scientific Committee (SEA) points out that users of portable music devices, who listen to music at full volume (more than 89 decibels) for 5 hours per week, exceed the limits currently in force relating to the maximum noise level agreed at the workplace.
Those who listen to music in such conditions for prolonged periods of time are at risk of permanent loss of hearing capacity after 5 years.
This is of interest to 5-10% of the users of these devices, and their number can be quantified around 2.5 and 10 million people in the EU.
