. Paradoxically, indeed, when we were convinced that we were now entering the realm of the network, of ever more sophisticated technology, of non-material, convinced that globalized finance was now destined to dominate the world, we realized at once, that our future will, on the contrary, have to settle its accounts more and more with things that are not very material, such as water, crops, oil.
