Open Office, this is the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
It's the day of the release of OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from home to office, from professionals to public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
Following almost a year-long work, carried out by volunteer developers, monitored by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office package shows up to the general public with various new features: from the welcome screen, and the interface revised and becoming less austere, to other more important ones, such as compatibility born for the Apple Mac OS X operating system, and the support for the new ODF (Open Document Format) format.
Open Office paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open the documents with the new extension of Microsoft (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting are some module-specific functions, such as the one that reduces the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, which is useful for sending them by e-mail, or for importing PDF files into the graphics development module, retaining the original appearance of the page.
Still on this front, it is possible to create "hybrid PDF" documents that combine the typical graph of the Adobe format with the elements of a spreadsheet or text developer.
Multi-person collaboration is an element that has had various improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoid conflicts over modifications, in the development of texts, because to each collaborator is assigned a commentary color for better recognition in the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring some of OpenOffice functions on the cloud, and in the coming weeks they are expected to deliver the final result.
The Italian version can be unloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.htmlet and is in addition to the English version on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, the sequel is, as usual, also available, for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD may be shipped to home or at the workplace.
And if the subject of free education can be a means of disseminating it in the houses, it is precisely in business that Open Office the continuation tries the great challenge, which can already count on various projects carried out in public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a training, consultation and assistance service, ideal for small and medium-sized enterprises, which could also open up to business foresight.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for Word's equivalent video writing; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for rival PowerPoint presentations; Dbase, like the famous Access, is the program that allows you to work on databases; finally Drwa is the graphics module.
Target for 2008, reaching 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is likely that with the release of the new version, we can even exceed the planned figure.
